# GNIF Trope Concept: Mainstream Media Silence
$schema: "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BelongieLab/gnif-taxonomy/main/schemas/trope-schema-v1.1.0.json"

tropeID: "gnif:trope:belongielab:MainstreamMediaSilence"
prefLabel: "Mainstream Media Silence"
altLabels:
  - "MSM Blackout"
  - "Why Isn't the Media Talking About This"

definition: >
  The assertion that major news organizations are deliberately ignoring or suppressing a specific story to protect an agenda or group.

description: >
  A highly viral social media trope used to artificially inflate the perceived importance of a story or to foster in-group solidarity. Ironically, the trope is frequently deployed alongside links to the very mainstream media articles it claims do not exist, or persists long after widespread coverage has begun. It capitalizes on the audience's baseline distrust of institutional media.

comments: >
  Often functions as a distribution mechanism rather than pure commentary; appending "the media won't show you this" to a video is a known algorithmic engagement hack.

relationships:
  parentTrope: "gnif:trope:belongielab:MediaCritique"
  relatedTropes:
    - "gnif:trope:belongielab:BuriedLead"
    - "gnif:trope:belongielab:EstablishmentCoverup"
